# Backend Testing

## Purpose

This rule defines testing strategy, structure, and standards for the FastAPI backend using pytest, test doubles, and async test patterns.

Tests protect business rules, document behavior, and enable safe refactoring across `apps/api/app/features/`.

---

## Scope

Applies to:

- Test packages mirroring feature structure under `apps/api/tests/` or `apps/api/app/features/<feature>/tests/`
- Unit tests for domain and application layers
- Integration tests for repositories and API endpoints
- Test fixtures, factories, and fakes
- Coverage expectations for critical commerce paths

Does not apply to:

- Frontend E2E tests (Playwright — see `playwright-e2e-checkout` skill)
- Load testing infrastructure
- Manual QA checklists
- Production monitoring (see logging/observability)

---

## Core Principles

Always:

- Test domain logic without database or HTTP (fast unit tests)
- Test use cases with faked repositories and gateways
- Test repositories against real PostgreSQL in integration tests (Docker/test DB)
- Test API endpoints with `httpx.AsyncClient` and FastAPI app fixture
- Use factories for test data (`OrderFactory`, `ProductFactory`)
- Name tests by behavior: `test_place_order_raises_when_insufficient_stock`
- Isolate tests: no shared mutable state; transactional rollback per test when using DB
- Mark slow tests (`@pytest.mark.integration`) for selective CI runs

Never:

- Mock domain entities under test
- Hit production databases or external APIs in CI
- Assert implementation details (private method call counts) over behavior
- Skip tests for payment, auth, and checkout critical paths
- Use sleep-based timing for async; use `pytest-asyncio` and proper awaits
- Duplicate production business logic inside test helpers

---

## Test Pyramid

### Unit Tests (Majority)

Location: `apps/api/app/features/<feature>/tests/unit/`

Targets:

- Entities and value objects
- Domain services
- Application use cases with fakes

Speed: milliseconds. No I/O.

### Integration Tests

Location: `apps/api/app/features/<feature>/tests/integration/`

Targets:

- SQLAlchemy repositories against test PostgreSQL
- Cache adapters against test Redis (optional testcontainers)
- Migrations compatibility smoke

### API Tests

Location: `apps/api/tests/api/` or feature integration folder

Targets:

- HTTP status codes, response schema, auth enforcement
- End-to-end within monolith boundary (router → use case → DB)

Use dependency overrides to inject test doubles where appropriate.

---

## Test Double Strategy

| Dependency | Unit Test | Integration Test |
|------------|-----------|------------------|
| Repository | Fake in memory | Real DB |
| External payment API | Fake gateway | Contract test / recorded fixtures |
| Event publisher | Spy/list fake | Optional integration |
| Clock/time | Injected fixed clock | Real time OK |

Fakes implement same protocol as production adapters.

```python
class FakeOrderRepository:
    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self._orders: dict[OrderId, Order] = {}

    async def get_by_id(self, order_id: OrderId, session: Any) -> Order | None:
        return self._orders.get(order_id)
```

---

## FastAPI Testing Pattern

```python
@pytest.fixture
async def client(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[AsyncClient]:
    async with AsyncClient(app=app, base_url="http://test") as ac:
        yield ac

async def test_place_order_returns_201(client: AsyncClient, auth_headers: dict) -> None:
    response = await client.post("/api/v1/orders", json={...}, headers=auth_headers)
    assert response.status_code == 201
    assert response.json()["id"]
```

Override dependencies:

```python
app.dependency_overrides[get_place_order_use_case] = lambda: fake_use_case
```

Always clear overrides after test.

---

## Async Testing

- Use `pytest-asyncio` with `asyncio_mode = auto` or explicit markers
- Await all coroutines; no un-awaited coroutine warnings
- Use same async session patterns as production in integration tests

---

## Critical Path Coverage

Mandatory test coverage areas:

- Authentication and authorization denial
- Checkout: cart → order → payment webhook idempotency
- Inventory reservation conflicts
- Validation errors (422) and domain errors (409/404)
- Repository mapping round-trip for core aggregates

---

## Decision Rules

IF testing business invariant
THEN unit test entity/value object directly.

IF testing orchestration order (call inventory before persist)
THEN unit test use case with spies/fakes.

IF testing SQL correctness
THEN integration test repository with test DB.

IF testing HTTP contract
THEN API test with AsyncClient.

IF external API contract critical (Stripe webhook)
THEN contract test with official fixture payloads.

IF test requires sleep > 1s
THEN redesign with injected clock or event-driven assertion.

---

## Anti-Patterns

Never create:

- Tests that depend on execution order
- Shared DB state without cleanup between tests
- `@patch` everywhere instead of designed fakes
- 100% coverage chasing on trivial getters
- Snapshot tests of entire JSON responses that hide intentional changes
- Skipped tests (`pytest.skip`) without ticket reference indefinitely
- Testing only happy path on payment flows

---

## Validation Checklist

Before completing feature work verify:

✓ Domain rules have unit tests.

✓ Use cases tested with fakes for failure and success paths.

✓ Repositories have integration tests for main queries.

✓ API tests cover auth, validation, and error mapping.

✓ Tests run in CI with deterministic results.

✓ No production external calls in tests.

✓ Factories/fixtures reduce duplication.

✓ Critical commerce flows covered.

✓ Async tests properly awaited.

